# Page Template: Detail Page

Reference structure for entity detail pages in **{{ display_name }}**.

Design style: **{{ design_style }}**

---

## Purpose

A detail page shows all information about a single entity. It answers "everything I need to know about X." It also provides the primary entry point for editing, status transitions, and related actions.

---

## Layout Structure

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Breadcrumbs: Home / Entities / Entity Name              │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Entity Header                                           │
│  ┌──────────┐  Entity Name (h1)                         │
│  │  Avatar  │  Sub-label (status badge, entity type)     │
│  │  or Icon │  Meta: Created 14 Mar 2025 by Alice        │
│  └──────────┘                             [Edit] [More v]│
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Tab Bar: [Overview] [Activity] [Related Items] [Files]  │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                          │
│  TAB: Overview                                           │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────┐ ┌────────────────────┐│
│  │  Details Section             │ │  Sidebar Panel     ││
│  │  Field  Value                │ │  Status            ││
│  │  Field  Value                │ │  Assignee          ││
│  │  Field  Value                │ │  Tags              ││
│  │                              │ │  Quick Actions     ││
│  │  Description / Notes         │ └────────────────────┘│
│  └──────────────────────────────┘                        │
│                                                          │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## Section Breakdown

### Breadcrumbs

Always show the full path to the current entity. The last item is the current page (not a link).

```
Home / [Entity List Name] / [Entity Name]
```

- Use `aria-label="Breadcrumb"` on the `<nav>` element
- Separate items with `aria-hidden="true"` separator characters (not `>` as text content)
- On mobile, collapse to show only the parent level

{% if router == "app-router" %}
```tsx
// src/components/ui/Breadcrumbs.tsx
import Link from "next/link";

interface Crumb {
  label: string;
  href?: string;
}

export function Breadcrumbs({ crumbs }: { crumbs: Crumb[] }) {
  return (
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol className="flex items-center gap-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        {crumbs.map((crumb, i) => (
          <li key={i} className="flex items-center gap-1">
            {i > 0 && <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>}
            {crumb.href ? (
              <Link href={crumb.href} className="hover:text-foreground">
                {crumb.label}
              </Link>
            ) : (
              <span className="text-foreground font-medium" aria-current="page">
                {crumb.label}
              </span>
            )}
          </li>
        ))}
      </ol>
    </nav>
  );
}
```
{% endif %}

### Entity Header

The header conveys identity at a glance. It contains:

- **Avatar or icon**: Entity visual representation (image, initials fallback, or domain icon)
- **Name (h1)**: The entity's primary identifier - always an `<h1>` (only one per page)
- **Status badge**: Coloured badge showing current state (Active, Pending, Archived, etc.)
- **Meta row**: Created date, modified date, owner/author
- **Action buttons (top-right):**
  - Primary action: "Edit" (or the most common operation)
  - Secondary actions: collapsed into a "More" dropdown (Delete, Archive, Export, etc.)

{% if design_style == "minimal-clean" %}
**Style guidance (minimal-clean):**
- Clean horizontal layout with generous spacing
- Status badge: small rounded pill, background tint of status colour
- Action buttons: outlined or ghost, not filled (the content is the focus)
{% elif design_style == "corporate-professional" %}
**Style guidance (corporate-professional):**
- Header has a light background panel separating it from the content
- Status prominently displayed in a structured badge
- Edit button is a filled primary button
- Metadata in a small, structured grid below the title
{% elif design_style == "playful-modern" %}
**Style guidance (playful-modern):**
- Colourful avatar background based on entity initials
- Status uses emoji or icon alongside text
- Rounded action buttons with hover animations
{% endif %}

### Tab Bar

Tabs divide the entity's content into logical sections to avoid overwhelming the user.

**Standard tabs for most entities:**

| Tab | Content |
|-----|---------|
| Overview | Primary fields, description, key metadata |
| Activity | Audit log, comments, timeline of changes |
| Related Items | Linked entities (e.g. invoices on a customer) |
| Files / Attachments | Documents, images attached to the entity |

**Tab implementation rules:**
- URL must reflect active tab so it is shareable: `/users/123?tab=activity`
- Keyboard navigable (`ArrowLeft` / `ArrowRight` between tabs, `Enter` / `Space` to activate)
- Tab content is lazy-loaded - do not fetch all tab data upfront

```tsx
// URL-synced tab state (App Router)
"use client";
import { useSearchParams, useRouter } from "next/navigation";

const tabs = ["overview", "activity", "related", "files"] as const;
type Tab = typeof tabs[number];

function useActiveTab(): [Tab, (tab: Tab) => void] {
  const searchParams = useSearchParams();
  const router = useRouter();
  const tab = (searchParams.get("tab") ?? "overview") as Tab;
  const setTab = (t: Tab) => router.push(`?tab=${t}`, { scroll: false });
  return [tab, setTab];
}
```

### Overview Tab: Details Section

The main content area for field/value pairs.

- Use a two-column definition list pattern for structured fields
- Group related fields with a section heading
- Long text fields (notes, description) get their own full-width row
- Editable fields show a pencil icon on hover that opens an inline edit or the edit form

### Overview Tab: Sidebar Panel

The sidebar provides at-a-glance status and quick actions without navigating away.

**Typical sidebar content:**

- Current status with a change control (dropdown to transition state)
- Assignee / owner with reassign action
- Tags or labels with add/remove
- Quick links to related entities
- Timestamps (created, updated, due date)

