## Empty and Error States

| Scenario | Treatment |
|----------|-----------|
| Entity not found | `notFound()` renders the 404 page |
| Permission denied | Redirect to login or render a 403 message with contact instructions |
| Tab data fails to load | Inline error with "Retry" button; other tabs remain functional |
| No related items | Illustration + "No [related items] yet" + add button |
| No activity yet | "No activity recorded yet" - not an error, just empty |

---

## Responsiveness

| Viewport | Layout |
|----------|--------|
| < 768 px | Single column: sidebar moves below details |
| 768 - 1023 px | Two-column, but sidebar is narrower |
| >= 1024 px | Full side-by-side layout |

Tab bar scrolls horizontally on small screens rather than wrapping or truncating.

---

## Actions: Destructive Operations

- **Delete** and other destructive actions must be behind a confirmation dialog
- Confirmation dialog states the entity name explicitly ("Are you sure you want to delete John Smith?")
- Use `role="alertdialog"` for confirmation dialogs
- Primary button in the confirmation dialog is styled red/destructive
- The cancel button is the default focused element (safer default)
